This year marks my 25th year of being a happy immigrant, self-employed, married with no kids, vegetarian and living in Canada. Oh life has been good… seems almost too good to be true. Time to take stock of my life and sought into it for the tiniest, vanishingly small flaw, because everything else seems too perfect. I try these days to do something “must do” every day. As a first step, I try to call my friend wherever he is. I’m sorry, my friend lives hundreds of time away from me on this planet, I think he doesn’t want to talk to me, so I don’t try anymore unless I have an important message to pass on.
